cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on the application of deep learning methods for brain tissue segmentation in MRI, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and fully convolutional neural networks (FCNNs) also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of overlapping as a sampling strategy, which relates to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of multiple datasets and imaging modalities suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
